{{Infobox language |name=Tumtum |states=[[Sudan]] |region=[[Kordofan]] |speakers={{sigfig|7,300|1}}<!--data supports 1 sig fig--> |date=no date |ref=e10<!--5,200 (Welmers 1971) in Ethn.08--> |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam1=[[Kadu languages|Kadu]] |fam2=Eastern |iso3=tbr |glotto=tumt1243 |glottorefname=Tumtum }} '''Tumtum''' is a [[Kadu languages|Kadu language]] spoken in [[Kordofan]]. Dialects are Karondi (Kurondi, Korindi), Talassa, and Tumtum proper.
